result.execSummary:
The defendant Jessica M Carli was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Harboring/Aiding a Felon-Falsify Info (A/B/C/D) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.47(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

of Sentencing Hearing held on 08-23-17

Defendant Jessica M Carli in court with attorney Vincent Kurta.  Richard J. Dufour appeared for the State of Wisconsin, Officer Jason Geach also present.   AG calls case at 12:56 a.m.  Cites appearances.  AG Dufour acknowledges PSI recieved.  Has individuals who want to speak.  Court will allow.  Atty Kurta requests guidance re exhibits (records).   Per Court, can seal.  AG Dufour has no objection but wants opportunity to review.  Court informed Atty Haukaas delayed.  Atty Kurta ready to proceed.  1:00 p.m.  Sue H. reads VIS from her brother and one of her own.  1:06 p.m.  Terry B. reads VIS on behalf of self and "TC".  1:10 p.m.  Lisa H. gives VIS.  AG Dufour preserves argument for later.  Per Court, Atty Kurta's motion for witnesses to appear via phone was granted.    Calls the following witnesses:  1:13 p.m. Leslie Berg appears via phone.  Witness sworn in by Judge.  Direct by Vince Kurta.  1:17 p.m.  Cross by Dufour.  1:17 p.m.  No redirect.  1:19 p.m.  Susan A. appears via phone.  Witness sworn in by Judge.  Direct by Atty Kurta.  1:20 p.m.  Cross by AG Dufour.  No redirect.  1:23 p.m.  Monica C. appears via phone.  Sworn in by Judge.  Direct by Atty Kurta.  No cross.   1:26 p.m.  John C. sworn in by Judge.  Gives statement.  No cross.  1:29 p.m.  Rose S. gives statement.  1:37 p.m.  Nayah E. gives statement.  1:40 p.m.  Chris E. gives statement.  No questions from counsel.  1:43 p.m.  No further witnesses.  1:44 p.m.  AG Dufour argues sentencing.  1:59 p.m.  Atty Kurta argues sentencing.  Both attorneys address PSI.  2:20 p.m.  Court advises def of right of allocution.  Def reads statement.  2:23 p.m.  Court addresses parties.  Sentences defendant to 8 years in the Wisconsin Prison System with 4 years of Initial Confinement followed by 4 years of Extended Supervision.  Deems defendant eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program and Substance Abuse Program.  Written Explanation document to be provided to def.  Court also imposes recommendation of DOC on page 24 of PSI which include: no contact with immediate family of Lisa W., no contact with Donald Rick, shall not possess/consume alcoholic beverages, illegal drugs, drug paraphernalia or any mind altering substances, complete mental health assessment and comply with any recommendations of mental health care professionals, complete Cognitive Interventions Programming, complete any other assessment or treatment deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.  No credit for time served.  Adj.  2:35 p.m.  klr

Defendant Jessica M Carli in court with attorney Craig Haukaas.  Richard J. Dufour appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Dufour calls case at 1:29 p.m.  Addresses court re sentence recommendation.  Attorney Haukaas, free to argue sentencing, not a joint recommendation.  Def pleads NC to sole count.  Defendant's decision, no coercion.  PLQ filed.  Court addresses def re same.  Admits signing and giving answers without coercion.  Atty Dufour addresses "hiding" evidence versus "destroying".  Not destroying.  Atty Haukaas satisfied def freely, intelligently and knowingly pleads.  Court finds factual basis to accept plea and does so.  Finds def guilty of Count #1.  Attorney Haukaas requests a PSI.  AG requests bond to continue.  Per Court, bond continues.  PSI to be conducted per Court.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 23, 2017 at 1:00 p.m.  Adjourned at 1:36 p.m.  klr
